<item>
            <title>[LU-296] File test for $TF_FAIL should be double quoted</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-296</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The file test for $TF_FAIL variable should be quoted in acceptance-small.sh and auster.sh. Otherwise, if this variable is not defined, bash will spit out something like&lt;br/&gt;
acceptance-small.sh: line 123: [: too many arguments&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Bash variables should generally be quoted whenever they are referenced. (see &lt;a href=&quot;http://tldp.org/LDP/abs/html/quotingvar.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://tldp.org/LDP/abs/html/quotingvar.html&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
